      Registration automation is a core component. AI-powered systems process sign-ups, manage payments, and trigger personalized communication sequences. They can also initiate abandoned cart recovery workflows, re-engaging potential attendees who didn't complete the process. For vendor and stakeholder coordination, AI centralizes communications and automates tasks like scheduling, resource allocation, and sending real-time updates, ensuring all parties are synchronized. The technology must support hybrid events and offer multi-language capabilities to cater to a global audience, making it a versatile solution for modern event challenges.
    </p>

